Beyond The Stars provides what Blue Note recording artist Nduduzo Makhathini describes in his liner notes as a divine summary of Bheki's life story: a sonic pilgrimage from the beautiful and organic landscapes of Durban, to the vibrant energy of London and ultimately toward the inner dimensions of ones being.

He died in his London flat, having spent most of his last years back in South Africa, but without finding an outlet for his skills there; his home was burgled in 1994, which affected him deeply, due to the loss of the mouthpiece John Coltrane had used for the recording of A Love Supreme, given to him by Alice Coltrane at Newport.
